### Description

In Taiga UI we have these styles:
```less
.interactive(@ruleset) {
    // TODO switch to :is after Safari 14 and FF 78 support
    &:-webkit-any(a, button, select, textarea, input, label) {
        @ruleset();
    }

    &:-moz-any(a, button, select, textarea, input, label) {
        @ruleset();
    }
}
```
These are old versions of `:is()` CSS selector for Safari and Firefox:
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:is#browser_compatibility

Angular should not display warnings when using them:
![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/11832552/37391def-73fd-41fd-95d1-bddc9267eb10)


